<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-06-15T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-06-15T17:00:00-05:00" n="49" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d49">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">760c.60f/11: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wallace</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-06-15T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 15,
                                            1920—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>1117. Your telegram 1279, June 12th, 6 P.M.</p>
                            <p>This Government has no objection to decision of the conference of
                                Ambassadors in regard to the plan of arbitration to determine the
                                attribution of the Duchy of Teschen thus renouncing plebiscite
                                provided governments of Poland and Czechoslovakia agree. The
                                Department has so informed Legations at Prague and Warsaw.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>